3 Partook in the half priced burger deal with purchase of a beverage which is in effect all day on Saturday. The burger had to be sent back the first time (well a new one was made and old one was left in front of me) for being undercooked. Happens all the time with my well done standards, so not a big deal. Overall, nothing really set this bacon cheeseburger apart from any other burger on the block. Bun was supposedly homemade, but I really doubt that fact and bacon was run of the mill meat. I guess the onion rings were pretty good and the chipotle mayo kicks butt on their watery herb mayo.       The place does stand out with their TV sets though as a good dozen or more line the wall for perfect side by side viewing of multiple games. Seems like their is always a special or two whether happy hour or not ($3 San Tan's last night), so will be back for other grub and sports.  Skip the chili - it is flavorless and overloaded with tomatoes. A nothing dish.
